 Msobomvu police on Wednesday morning arrested a 36-year-old man for dealing in dagga. "The suspect was arrested at about 06:30 at Booi Farm, Butterworth," described police spokesperson Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect was found with dagga that has weight of 7.518kg with a street value of R8 000." Captain Manatha said that the suspect was arrested after police intelligence indicated that he was dealing in dagga. "The suspect was out on bail in another case of dealing in dagga. "He will appear before the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Thursday on a charge of dealing in dagga," he said. Image: Members of Msobomvu Police Station with recovered dagga of the suspect. 